
→ Linux/X/keyboard-extension

{ Components

  { Display server

    Responsible for the *graphical environment*.

    Implementations: Xorg, XFree86 and X11.

  }
  { Display manager #x-display-manager
   
    If the system starts up, this is the first program (after running the display server?)
    -
    The display manager allows a user to login in (hence, the display manager is also known as »login manager«).
    -
    When the user is logged in, the display manager starts an X-Session.

    Implementations: GDM (Gnome), KDM, Xdm, LightDM, SLiM (Sipmle Login Manager), qingy etc.

  }
  { Window manager #x-window-manager

    The window manager is concerned with how (application-)windows look like and where they are created.

    Some window manager need a desktop environment, others, such as WindowMaker, sawfish, fvwm etc don't.
    
    Other implementations: metacity (practically unusable without GNOME), twm …

  }
  { Desktop environment

    A desktop environment tries to create a consistent exprience for the user. Thus, it ships with a set of applications.

    Implementations: XFCE, KDE, GNOME

  }

}

sa:
  → Linux/fhs/etc/X11,
  → Linux/fhs/usr/share/X11
